text:
The theory I heard there in Panama is that Kriss and Lisanne were ABDUCTED that same afternoon, either on the El Pianista trail or upon returning from the trailâ€” a witness said the girls were getting into a red pickup truck on the road at the end of the dayâ€”and that the girls DIDN'T MAKE the emergency calls because their attackers took their cell phones. 
The idea is that their attackers dialed the emergency numbers TO CREATE a story of disorientation in the jungle, to make people believe the girls were lost in the jungle or had an accident. That's the most credible theory; that's why there are no photos of them lost or injured, nor any messages from them to their parents or boyfriends. 
And regarding the LAST PHOTOS taken with the camera eight days later, the explanation is SIMILAR.
The Dutch investigator said on television that those pictures must have been taken by the criminals, their captors, trying to light the way with the flash in the wee hours. One of those photos was a photo of Kriss's hair, apparently from the back of her head. By that time, the girls were gone; they had been murdered
